public class Fields
extends java.lang.Object

This is the class container for all recorded data. This object is used in conjunction with DataFieldManager to store one line of data at a time. USAGE: Place data into the respective containers of this object, such as: 

 myFieldsObject.timeMillis = System.currentTimeMillis();
You may then use your DataFieldManager instances's putData() function to record the data placed into this Field instance's containers. After calling that function, you may replace the information in the container's to set up a new line of data to record and repeat the process for all data lines to be recorded.
